{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1759,"text":"I worked as a war reporter for 15 years"},{"time":5136,"text":"before I realized\nthat I really had a problem."},{"time":9101,"text":"There was something really wrong with me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":11231,"text":"This was about a year before 9/11,\nand America wasn't at war yet."},{"time":15432,"text":"We weren't talking about PTSD."},{"time":17848,"text":"We were not yet talking\nabout the effect of trauma and war"},{"time":22068,"text":"on the human psyche."},{"time":24706,"text":"I'd been in Afghanistan\nfor a couple of months"},{"time":26980,"text":"with the Northern Alliance\nas they were fighting the Taliban."},{"time":30012,"text":"And at that point the Taliban\nhad an air force,"},{"time":33293,"text":"they had fighter planes,\nthey had tanks, they had artillery,"},{"time":36546,"text":"and we really got hammered\npretty badly a couple of times."},{"time":39861,"text":"We saw some very ugly things."},{"time":43104,"text":"But I didn't really think it affected me."},{"time":45098,"text":"I didn't think much about it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":46650,"text":"I came home to New York, where I live."},{"time":49141,"text":"Then one day I went down into the subway,"},{"time":52490,"text":"and for the first time in my life,"},{"time":54965,"text":"I knew real fear."},{"time":56823,"text":"I had a massive panic attack."},{"time":60058,"text":"I was way more scared\nthan I had ever been in Afghanistan."},{"time":64093,"text":"Everything I was looking at seemed like\nit was going to kill me,"},{"time":67517,"text":"but I couldn't explain why."},{"time":70121,"text":"The trains were going too fast."},{"time":72119,"text":"There were too many people."},{"time":73497,"text":"The lights were too bright."},{"time":75309,"text":"Everything was too loud,\neverything was moving too quickly."},{"time":78132,"text":"I backed up against a support column\nand just waited for it."},{"time":83115,"text":"When I couldn't take it any longer,\nI ran out of the subway station"},{"time":86335,"text":"and walked wherever I was going."}]},{"cues":[{"time":89648,"text":"Later, I found out that what I had\nwas short-term PTSD:"},{"time":93851,"text":"post-traumatic stress disorder."},{"time":96993,"text":"We evolved as animals, as primates,\nto survive periods of danger,"},{"time":100245,"text":"and if your life has been in danger,"},{"time":103190,"text":"you want to react to unfamiliar noises."},{"time":107352,"text":"You want to sleep lightly, wake up easily."},{"time":109631,"text":"You want to have nightmares and flashbacks"},{"time":111849,"text":"of the thing that could kill you."},{"time":114756,"text":"You want to be angry because it makes you\npredisposed to fight,"},{"time":117837,"text":"or depressed, because it keeps you out\nof circulation a little bit."},{"time":121591,"text":"Keeps you safe."},{"time":123580,"text":"It's not very pleasant,\nbut it's better than getting eaten."}]},{"cues":[{"time":128469,"text":"Most people recover\nfrom that pretty quickly."},{"time":130947,"text":"It takes a few weeks, a few months."},{"time":133061,"text":"I kept having panic attacks,\nbut they eventually went away."},{"time":136200,"text":"I had no idea it was connected\nto the war that I'd seen."},{"time":138874,"text":"I just thought I was going crazy,"},{"time":140494,"text":"and then I thought, well,\nnow I'm not going crazy anymore."}]},{"cues":[{"time":145197,"text":"About 20 percent of people, however,"},{"time":147851,"text":"wind up with chronic, long-term PTSD."},{"time":151166,"text":"They are not adapted to temporary danger."},{"time":153584,"text":"They are maladapted for everyday life,"},{"time":156369,"text":"unless they get help."},{"time":157994,"text":"We know that the people\nwho are vulnerable to long-term PTSD"},{"time":161557,"text":"are people who were abused as children,"},{"time":164297,"text":"who suffered trauma as children,"},{"time":166052,"text":"people who have low education levels,"},{"time":168694,"text":"people who have psychiatric\ndisorders in their family."},{"time":171276,"text":"If you served in Vietnam"},{"time":172578,"text":"and your brother is schizophrenic,"},{"time":175296,"text":"you're way more likely to get\nlong-term PTSD from Vietnam."}]},{"cues":[{"time":180571,"text":"So I started to study this\nas a journalist,"},{"time":183868,"text":"and I realized that there was something\nreally strange going on."},{"time":187415,"text":"The numbers seemed to be going\nin the wrong direction."},{"time":190597,"text":"Every war that we have\nfought as a country,"},{"time":192993,"text":"starting with the Civil War,"},{"time":194991,"text":"the intensity of the combat has gone down."},{"time":198878,"text":"As a result, the casualty rates\nhave gone down."},{"time":202707,"text":"But disability rates have gone up."},{"time":204686,"text":"They should be going\nin the same direction,"},{"time":207702,"text":"but they're going in different directions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":212124,"text":"The recent wars in Iraq and Afghanistan\nhave produced, thank God,"},{"time":216737,"text":"a casualty rate about one third\nof what it was in Vietnam."},{"time":224129,"text":"But they've also created --"},{"time":226678,"text":"they've also produced\nthree times the disability rates."},{"time":231526,"text":"Around 10 percent of the US military\nis actively engaged in combat,"},{"time":238439,"text":"10 percent or under."},{"time":239801,"text":"They're shooting at people,\nkilling people,"},{"time":242099,"text":"getting shot at,\nseeing their friends get killed."},{"time":244461,"text":"It's incredibly traumatic."},{"time":246038,"text":"But it's only about 10 percent\nof our military."},{"time":248872,"text":"But about half of our military has filed"},{"time":251129,"text":"for some kind of PTSD compensation\nfrom the government."}]},{"cues":[{"time":256922,"text":"And suicide doesn't even fit into this\nin a very logical way."},{"time":262173,"text":"We've all heard the tragic statistic\nof 22 vets a day, on average,"},{"time":267983,"text":"in this country, killing themselves."},{"time":271564,"text":"Most people don't realize"},{"time":273078,"text":"that the majority of those suicides\nare veterans of the Vietnam War,"},{"time":278739,"text":"that generation,"},{"time":280641,"text":"and their decision to take their own lives\nactually might not be related"},{"time":285163,"text":"to the war they fought 50 years earlier."},{"time":289122,"text":"In fact, there's no statistical connection\nbetween combat and suicide."},{"time":292838,"text":"If you're in the military\nand you're in a lot of combat,"},{"time":295929,"text":"you're no more likely to kill yourself\nthan if you weren't."},{"time":299614,"text":"In fact, one study found"},{"time":300964,"text":"that if you deploy to Iraq or Afghanistan,"},{"time":303012,"text":"you're actually slightly less likely\nto commit suicide later."}]},{"cues":[{"time":308626,"text":"I studied anthropology in college."},{"time":310920,"text":"I did my fieldwork\non the Navajo reservation."},{"time":313963,"text":"I wrote a thesis on Navajo\nlong-distance runners."},{"time":318473,"text":"And recently, while\nI was researching PTSD,"},{"time":323501,"text":"I had this thought."},{"time":326325,"text":"I thought back to the work\nI did when I was young,"},{"time":329428,"text":"and I thought, I bet the Navajo,\nthe Apache, the Comanche --"},{"time":333521,"text":"I mean, these are very warlike nations --"},{"time":336109,"text":"I bet they weren't getting\nPTSD like we do."},{"time":340814,"text":"When their warriors came back\nfrom fighting the US military"},{"time":343830,"text":"or fighting each other,"},{"time":346241,"text":"I bet they pretty much just slipped\nright back into tribal life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":351635,"text":"And maybe what determines"},{"time":353913,"text":"the rate of long-term PTSD"},{"time":356631,"text":"isn't what happened out there,"},{"time":359942,"text":"but the kind of society you come back to."},{"time":363107,"text":"And maybe if you come back\nto a close, cohesive, tribal society,"},{"time":368823,"text":"you can get over trauma pretty quickly."},{"time":371830,"text":"And if you come back\nto an alienating, modern society,"},{"time":376719,"text":"you might remain traumatized\nyour entire life."},{"time":380248,"text":"In other words, maybe the problem\nisn't them, the vets;"},{"time":383383,"text":"maybe the problem is us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":387325,"text":"Certainly, modern society\nis hard on the human psyche"},{"time":392649,"text":"by every metric that we have."},{"time":397043,"text":"As wealth goes up in a society,"},{"time":401523,"text":"the suicide rate goes up instead of down."},{"time":406066,"text":"If you live in modern society,"},{"time":408180,"text":"you're up to eight times more likely"},{"time":412379,"text":"to suffer from depression in your lifetime"},{"time":414724,"text":"than if you live in a poor,\nagrarian society."},{"time":418915,"text":"Modern society has probably produced\nthe highest rates of suicide"},{"time":422538,"text":"and depression and anxiety\nand loneliness and child abuse"},{"time":425816,"text":"ever in human history."},{"time":428695,"text":"I saw one study"},{"time":430292,"text":"that compared women in Nigeria,"},{"time":433358,"text":"one of the most chaotic\nand violent and corrupt"},{"time":436627,"text":"and poorest countries in Africa,"},{"time":439358,"text":"to women in North America."},{"time":440673,"text":"And the highest rates of depression\nwere urban women in North America."},{"time":445887,"text":"That was also the wealthiest group."}]},{"cues":[{"time":448637,"text":"So let's go back to the US military."},{"time":453096,"text":"Ten percent are in combat."},{"time":455638,"text":"Around 50 percent have filed\nfor PTSD compensation."},{"time":461602,"text":"So about 40 percent of veterans\nreally were not traumatized overseas"},{"time":467734,"text":"but have come home to discover\nthey are dangerously alienated"},{"time":472563,"text":"and depressed."},{"time":476341,"text":"So what is happening with them?"},{"time":479302,"text":"What's going on with those people,"},{"time":482051,"text":"the phantom 40 percent that are troubled\nbut don't understand why?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":486810,"text":"Maybe it's this:"},{"time":488158,"text":"maybe they had an experience\nof sort of tribal closeness"},{"time":492826,"text":"in their unit when they were overseas."},{"time":496075,"text":"They were eating together,\nsleeping together,"},{"time":498732,"text":"doing tasks and missions together."},{"time":501055,"text":"They were trusting each other\nwith their lives."},{"time":505160,"text":"And then they come home"},{"time":506857,"text":"and they have to give all that up"},{"time":509851,"text":"and they're coming back\nto a society, a modern society,"},{"time":513614,"text":"which is hard on people\nwho weren't even in the military."},{"time":517171,"text":"It's just hard on everybody."}]},{"cues":[{"time":519494,"text":"And we keep focusing on trauma, PTSD."},{"time":524685,"text":"But for a lot of these people,"},{"time":527340,"text":"maybe it's not trauma."},{"time":528561,"text":"I mean, certainly,\nsoldiers are traumatized"},{"time":531140,"text":"and the ones who are\nhave to be treated for that."},{"time":533533,"text":"But a lot of them --"},{"time":534751,"text":"maybe what's bothering them\nis actually a kind of alienation."},{"time":538321,"text":"I mean, maybe we just have\nthe wrong word for some of it,"},{"time":541115,"text":"and just changing our language,\nour understanding,"},{"time":543528,"text":"would help a little bit."},{"time":544726,"text":"\"Post-deployment alienation disorder.\""},{"time":547462,"text":"Maybe even just calling it that\nfor some of these people"},{"time":551634,"text":"would allow them to stop imagining"},{"time":554236,"text":"trying to imagine a trauma\nthat didn't really happen"},{"time":557707,"text":"in order to explain a feeling\nthat really is happening."},{"time":560502,"text":"And in fact, it's an extremely\ndangerous feeling."},{"time":563043,"text":"That alienation and depression\ncan lead to suicide."},{"time":565807,"text":"These people are in danger."},{"time":567828,"text":"It's very important to understand why."}]},{"cues":[{"time":571167,"text":"The Israeli military has a PTSD rate\nof around one percent."},{"time":575650,"text":"The theory is that everyone in Israel\nis supposed to serve in the military."},{"time":581273,"text":"When soldiers come back\nfrom the front line,"},{"time":583407,"text":"they're not going from a military\nenvironment to a civilian environment."},{"time":588741,"text":"They're coming back to a community\nwhere everyone understands"},{"time":593698,"text":"about the military."},{"time":594877,"text":"Everyone's been in it\nor is going to be in it."},{"time":597056,"text":"Everyone understands\nthe situation they're all in."},{"time":599436,"text":"It's as if they're all in one big tribe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":602282,"text":"We know that if you take a lab rat"},{"time":604340,"text":"and traumatize it and put it\nin a cage by itself,"},{"time":608036,"text":"you can maintain its trauma symptoms\nalmost indefinitely."},{"time":611717,"text":"And if you take that same lab rat\nand put it in a cage with other rats,"},{"time":618018,"text":"after a couple of weeks,\nit's pretty much OK."}]},{"cues":[{"time":623509,"text":"After 9/11,"},{"time":626549,"text":"the murder rate in New York City\nwent down by 40 percent."},{"time":629866,"text":"The suicide rate went down."},{"time":632756,"text":"The violent crime rate in New York\nwent down after 9/11."},{"time":637284,"text":"Even combat veterans of previous wars\nwho suffered from PTSD"},{"time":642627,"text":"said that their symptoms went down\nafter 9/11 happened."},{"time":647148,"text":"The reason is that if you traumatize\nan entire society,"},{"time":652450,"text":"we don't fall apart\nand turn on one another."},{"time":655693,"text":"We come together. We unify."},{"time":657831,"text":"Basically, we tribalize,"},{"time":659902,"text":"and that process of unifying\nfeels so good and is so good for us,"},{"time":665479,"text":"that it even helps people"},{"time":666920,"text":"who are struggling\nwith mental health issues."},{"time":670238,"text":"During the blitz in London,"},{"time":672027,"text":"admissions to psychiatric wards\nwent down during the bombings."}]},{"cues":[{"time":678606,"text":"For a while, that was the kind of country"},{"time":681852,"text":"that American soldiers came\nback to -- a unified country."},{"time":686288,"text":"We were sticking together."},{"time":687583,"text":"We were trying to understand\nthe threat against us."},{"time":690218,"text":"We were trying to help\nourselves and the world."},{"time":695521,"text":"But that's changed."},{"time":698392,"text":"Now, American soldiers,"},{"time":700762,"text":"American veterans are coming back\nto a country that is so bitterly divided"},{"time":705716,"text":"that the two political parties\nare literally accusing each other"},{"time":710670,"text":"of treason, of being\nan enemy of the state,"},{"time":714265,"text":"of trying to undermine the security\nand the welfare of their own country."},{"time":719049,"text":"The gap between rich and poor\nis the biggest it's ever been."},{"time":723206,"text":"It's just getting worse."},{"time":724415,"text":"Race relations are terrible."},{"time":726847,"text":"There are demonstrations\nand even riots in the streets"},{"time":729727,"text":"because of racial injustice."},{"time":732727,"text":"And veterans know that any tribe\nthat treated itself that way -- in fact,"},{"time":737012,"text":"any platoon that treated itself\nthat way -- would never survive."},{"time":743068,"text":"We've gotten used to it."},{"time":744983,"text":"Veterans have gone away\nand are coming back"},{"time":748860,"text":"and seeing their own country\nwith fresh eyes."},{"time":753325,"text":"And they see what's going on."},{"time":755738,"text":"This is the country they fought for."},{"time":758433,"text":"No wonder they're depressed."},{"time":760135,"text":"No wonder they're scared."}]},{"cues":[{"time":763371,"text":"Sometimes, we ask ourselves\nif we can save the vets."},{"time":768248,"text":"I think the real question\nis if we can save ourselves."},{"time":771905,"text":"If we can,"},{"time":773619,"text":"I think the vets are going to be fine."},{"time":776697,"text":"It's time for this country to unite,"},{"time":781818,"text":"if only to help the men and women\nwho fought to protect us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":787182,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":788437,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}